Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me produce the detailed implementation plan.

---

# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Overview

PulseBoard is an HTTP/WebSocket-based bulletin board platform. Its plugin mirrors the IRC plugin's architecture but replaces the IRC TCP client with HTTP calls and a WebSocket/polling monitor. Boards use a `$board-name` prefix (analogous to IRC `#channel`), direct messages use plain `username`. The text chunk limit is 4000 characters (matching Mattermost's default).

---

## 1. Complete File List

All files live under `extensions/pulseboard/`.

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── package.json                       # Package metadata with openclaw block
├── openclaw.plugin.json               # Plugin manifest
├── index.ts                           # defineChannelPluginEntry
├── setup-entry.ts                     # defineSetupPluginEntry
├── api.ts                             # Public barrel
├── channel-config-api.ts              # Re-exports PulseBoardChannelConfigSchema
├── runtime-api.ts                     # Private runtime barrel
└── src/
    ├── types.ts                       # Domain types
    ├── accounts.ts                    # resolveAccount, listAccountIds, etc.
    ├── config-schema.ts               # Zod schemas
    ├── normalize.ts                   # normalizeTarget, looksLikeId, allowlist
    ├── channel.ts                     # createChatChannelPlugin(...)
    ├── runtime.ts                     # createPluginRuntimeStore
    ├── send.ts                        # sendMessagePulseBoard
    ├── inbound.ts                     # handlePulseBoardInbound
    ├── monitor.ts                     # monitorPulseBoardProvider
    ├── probe.ts                       # probePulseBoard
    ├── setup-core.ts                  # pulseBoardSetupAdapter
    ├── setup-surface.ts               # pulseBoardSetupWizard
    ├── accounts.test.ts
    ├── config-schema.test.ts
    ├── normalize.test.ts
    ├── send.test.ts
    ├── channel.test.ts
    └── setup.test.ts
```

Total: 22 files.

---

## 2. File-by-File Details

### 2a. `extensions/pulseboard/package.json`

**Purpose:** Package metadata. The `openclaw` block drives CLI channel discovery, selection labels, docs path, and entry registration.

**Key content:**
```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
  "version": "2026.4.1-beta.1",
  "description": "OpenClaw PulseBoard channel plugin",
  "type": "module",
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "install": { "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1" },
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "pulseboard",
      "label": "PulseBoard",
      "selectionLabel": "PulseBoard (Server + Token)",
      "detailLabel": "PulseBoard",
      "docsPath": "/channels/pulseboard",
      "docsLabel": "pulseboard",
      "blurb": "real-time bulletin board with board (group) and direct messaging.",
      "aliases": ["pulse-board"],
      "systemImage": "text.bubble.fill"
    }
  }
}
```

No `dependencies` needed beyond those already available via the host workspace.

---

### 2b. `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json`

**Purpose:** Static manifest consumed by the plugin discovery system without executing plugin code.

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

---

### 2c. `extensions/pulseboard/index.ts`

**Purpose:** Channel entry point. Wires the plugin and its runtime setter into `defineChannelPluginEntry`.

**Key exports:** `pulseBoardPlugin`, `setPulseBoardRuntime` (re-exported), default export from `defineChannelPluginEntry`.

**Imports:**
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` → `defineChannelPluginEntry`, `ChannelPlugin`
- `./src/channel.js` → `pulseBoardPlugin`
- `./src/runtime.js` → `setPulseBoardRuntime`

```typescript
export default defineChannelPluginEntry({
  id: "pulseboard",
  name: "PulseBoard",
  description: "PulseBoard channel plugin",
  plugin: pulseBoardPlugin as ChannelPlugin,
  setRuntime: setPulseBoardRuntime,
});
```

---

### 2d. `extensions/pulseboard/setup-entry.ts`

**Purpose:** Setup entry point consumed by the setup CLI flow.

**Imports:** `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` → `defineSetupPluginEntry`; `./src/channel.js` → `pulseBoardPlugin`.

```typescript
export default defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin);
```

---

### 2e. `extensions/pulseboard/api.ts`

**Purpose:** Public barrel. Exposes accounts and setup surface for host use.

```typescript
export * from "./src/accounts.js";
export * from "./src/setup-surface.js";
```

---

### 2f. `extensions/pulseboard/channel-config-api.ts`

**Purpose:** Re-exports config schema for use by host config tooling.

```typescript
export { PulseBoardChannelConfigSchema } from "./src/config-schema.js";
```

---

### 2g. `extensions/pulseboard/runtime-api.ts`

**Purpose:** Private runtime barrel. Re-exports everything needed by `inbound.ts`, `send.ts`, and `monitor.ts` from SDK paths. Because PulseBoard is not a core channel, there is no `openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard` path. Instead all re-exports come directly from their canonical SDK subpaths.

**Key exports and sources:**

| Export | SDK path |
|---|---|
| `logInboundDrop`, `resolveMentionGatingWithBypass`, `dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-inbound` |
| `createChannelPairingController` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-pairing` |
| `GROUP_POLICY_BLOCKED_LABEL`, `resolveAllowlistProviderRuntimeGroupPolicy`, `resolveDefaultGroupPolicy`, `warnMissingProviderGroupPolicyFallbackOnce` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-group-policy` |
| `readStoreAllowFromForDmPolicy`, `resolveEffectiveAllowFromLists` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/security-runtime` |
| `buildBaseChannelStatusSummary`, `createAccountStatusSink` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers` (re-exported from `status-helpers` or a runtime status path — check actual export names during implementation) |
| `chunkTextForOutbound`, `deliverFormattedTextWithAttachments` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-outbound` or equivalent runtime path |
| `DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id` |
| `getChatChannelMeta` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` |
| `PAIRING_APPROVED_MESSAGE` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-pairing` |
| Type `BaseProbeResult`, `ChannelPlugin`, `DmPolicy`, `GroupPolicy`, `MarkdownConfig`, `OpenClawConfig`, `OutboundReplyPayload`, `PluginRuntime`, `RuntimeEnv`, `BlockStreamingCoalesceConfig`, `DmConfig`, `GroupToolPolicyConfig`, `GroupToolPolicyBySenderConfig` | from whichever SDK path carries them (follow IRC's pattern: many come from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc`; for PulseBoard use the actual public SDK paths) |

Implementation note: Because there is no `openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard`, you must import each symbol from the actual public SDK subpath where it lives. Verify each symbol against the public entrypoints listed in `scripts/lib/plugin-sdk-entrypoints.json` or the exported `.d.ts` files. Do not assume they all come from a single path.

---

### 2h. `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts`

**Purpose:** All PulseBoard-specific TypeScript types.

**Imports:** Types from `./runtime-api.js` (or a local `type` import of the barrel) for standard fields.

**Key type shapes:**

```typescript
// PulseBoardBoardConfig: per-board overrides (mirrors IrcChannelConfig)
export type PulseBoardBoardConfig = {
  requireMention?: boolean;
  tools?: GroupToolPolicyConfig;
  toolsBySender?: GroupToolPolicyBySenderConfig;
  skills?: string[];
  enabled?: boolean;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  systemPrompt?: string;
};

// PulseBoardAccountConfig: per-account settings
export type PulseBoardAccountConfig = {
  name?: string;
  enabled?: boolean;
  host?: string;               // Server URL, e.g. https://pb.example.com
  token?: string;              // API token (also from PULSEBOARD_TOKEN)
  username?: string;           // Bot username (also from PULSEBOARD_USERNAME)
  boards?: string[];           // Boards to subscribe to on startup, e.g. ["$general"]
  dmPolicy?: DmPolicy;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  groupPolicy?: GroupPolicy;
  groupAllowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  groups?: Record<string, PulseBoardBoardConfig>;
  markdown?: MarkdownConfig;
  textChunkLimit?: number;
  blockStreaming?: boolean;
  blockStreamingCoalesce?: BlockStreamingCoalesceConfig;
  responsePrefix?: string;
  dms?: Record<string, DmConfig>;
  // ReplyRuntimeConfigSchemaShape fields (historyLimit, etc.) also spread in
};

// PulseBoardConfig: top-level config (single account + multi-account)
export type PulseBoardConfig = PulseBoardAccountConfig & {
  accounts?: Record<string, PulseBoardAccountConfig>;
  defaultAccount?: string;
};

// CoreConfig: typed view of the full config object
export type CoreConfig = OpenClawConfig & {
  channels?: OpenClawConfig["channels"] & {
    pulseboard?: PulseBoardConfig;
  };
};

// PulseBoardInboundMessage: normalized inbound event from a board or DM
export type PulseBoardInboundMessage = {
  messageId: string;
  /** $board-name for group messages; sender username for DMs */
  target: string;
  senderUsername: string;
  text: string;
  timestamp: number;
  isGroup: boolean;
};

// PulseBoardProbe: result of a connectivity check
export type PulseBoardProbe = BaseProbeResult<string> & {
  host: string;
  username: string;
  latencyMs?: number;
};
```

---

### 2i. `extensions/pulseboard/src/accounts.ts`

**Purpose:** Account resolution — merges config, applies env var overrides, resolves credentials, returns a `ResolvedPulseBoardAccount`.

**Key exports:** `resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId`, `listPulseBoardAccountIds`, `resolveAccount` (or `resolvePulseBoardAccount`), `listEnabledPulseBoardAccounts`.

**Imports:**
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-helpers` → `createAccountListHelpers`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id` → `DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID`, `normalizeAccountId`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-resolution` → `resolveMergedAccountConfig`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input` → `normalizeResolvedSecretInputString`
