# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

Add a new fictional "PulseBoard" channel plugin to OpenClaw. PulseBoard is an imaginary real-time bulletin board platform where users post messages to named "boards" (group chat, prefix `$`) and send direct messages. The plugin must:

- Support `chatTypes: ["direct", "group"]` with a **4000-character** text chunk limit
- Follow the exact extension structure of existing bundled channel plugins (primarily IRC as reference)
- Create **only new files** inside `extensions/pulseboard/` — no existing files are touched
- Use only public `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` SDK paths (no `src/**` imports); since PulseBoard is not a core channel there is no `openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard` facade

Reference files studied:
- `extensions/irc/` (all files) — primary pattern reference
- `extensions/nostr/runtime-api.ts`, `src/plugin-sdk/nostr.ts` — non-core channel patterns
- `src/plugin-sdk/irc.ts` — maps SDK symbols to their canonical public paths
- `scripts/lib/plugin-sdk-entrypoints.json` — complete list of public SDK subpaths

---

